rComments: Lectures are really dry, and she posts in-class notes as well, so attendance is really up to u. First midterm easy, second one is hard with random-20-point discussion questions (there is even no specific grading rubric, guess just TA grading according to their liking). But the-3-hour final is easy again, and scheme shifts lower mt to final, so...

She is a nice teacher this year. She cares about her students. She answers email very fast. Her lectures are clear and the tests are fair. If you do the exercises before tests, you will get a good grade.
Worst prof in the department so far. Very disorganized and often cancels her office hour the day before. Not responsible.
The worst professor I have ever seen. The test is really hard compared with what she taught in class, or she just read the slides rather than teaching. The tests were so bad. Her class is so boring.
She is nice
Just reads the slides and does nothing else, most bs class i ever took, learned nothing
She is very bad at teaching, no help at all, refuses to curve marks  and curves down instead. She post practice solutions the day before a final, worst experience ever.

This prof is very disorganized, very hard to follow, lots of things throwing at you, doesn't prepare you well for the test and final. Her lecture is very boring. Throws too many curve ball questions on test and final, if you don't study, you are finished. Whatever you do, avoid this prof at all costs!!!
She is not a good prof at teaching, she mostly reads the slides and doesn't make the lecture at all interesting at all and her lecture is sometime disorganized, gives very hard test!!

Very lazy..always posts things late...refuses to post past exams, doesn't give solutions to problem sets even though its only a week away until finals. Complains all the time like she's the busiest person on earth. Very unorganized lectures. Nice job uoft, if this is what you call a professor then i want my 30k tuition back.

She is obviously teaching a subject that is out of her depth. Makes no effort to make the class interesting at all, just skims through the slides like a robot (trying to finish everything as fast as possible). Class material is very boring by nature, and she just makes it worse. After all, the Econ department is known for having incompetent profs.

Very unorganized, lectures are too confusing. Not very knowledgeable, I must say. She makes a lot of excuses (trying to make herself "look" busy) but cmon this is University and taking your kids to the dentist is not an excuse for posting slides late and not telling us the midterm format until TWO hours before the actual midterm itself. What a joke
Too disorganized lectures
Disorganized notes and lectures. Very weird term-tests.

Extremely disorganized, notes are in random order with a lot of mistakes, which later need to be corrected so you keep having to read the same set of slides to make sure you have the correct information. No logical order to teaching. Random facts and concepts thrown at you. Made a boring subject unbearable, so no one studied for the midterm.

I have never seen any other professor as lazy and irresponsible as her. She always posts slides after the lecture, and she even didn't inform us of the midterm format until two days before the test. She always makes excuses that she's very busy as a mother of little baby. But she keeps coming to class without preparation.
Nice lecturer but doesn't know much about corporate finance beyond theory.

She posts everything online.. very nice prof.  Very helpful.  I don't think her accent is bad.  Just do her practice problems and you will do well.  Pretty high class average.  Overall a pleasant experience.

Incredible Russian accent, but she does try to be very clear. Jumps through her slides, sometimes a bit disorganized, but goes out of her way to teach you things. One of the better professors in the Dept. of Economics at UofT.

The exam, although it was divided into different sections, seemed like 1 really long question because all the answers carried over to other questions, so if you made 1 mistake, you're screwed.  Otherwise, she's a good prof. that cares about her students and wants them to do well.  :)
